Class ShapeSorter<T extends Comparable<T>>

java.lang.Object
utilities.ShapeSorter<T>
Type Parameters:
T - type that implements Comparable interface
public class ShapeSorter<T extends Comparable<T>> extends Object
Generic sorting class that implements various sorting algorithms for arrays of Comparable objects. All sorts are implemented to sort in descending order.

  • Method Details

    • bubbleSort

      public void bubbleSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Bubble sort implementation. Repeatedly steps through the list, compares adjacent elements and swaps them if they are in the wrong order. Time Complexity: O(n²) Space Complexity: O(1)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • insertionSort

      public void insertionSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Insertion sort implementation. Builds final sorted array one item at a time by repeatedly taking next element and inserting it into its correct position. Time Complexity: O(n²) Space Complexity: O(1)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • selectionSort

      public void selectionSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Selection sort implementation. Divides input into sorted and unsorted regions, repeatedly finds minimum element from unsorted region and adds it to sorted region. Time Complexity: O(n²) Space Complexity: O(1)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • mergeSort

      public void mergeSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Merge sort implementation. Divides input array into two halves, recursively sorts them, then merges the sorted halves. Time Complexity: O(n log n) Space Complexity: O(n)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • merge

      private void merge(T[] shapes, T[] left, T[] right, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Helper method for merge sort. Merges two sorted arrays into a single sorted array.
      Parameters:
      shapes - destination array
      left - first sorted array
      right - second sorted array
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • quickSort

      public void quickSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Quick sort implementation. Selects a 'pivot' element and partitions other elements into two sub-arrays according to whether they are less than or greater than the pivot. Time Complexity: O(n log n) average case, O(n²) worst case Space Complexity: O(log n)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • quickSortRecursive

      private void quickSortRecursive(T[] shapes, int low, int high, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Recursive helper method for quick sort.
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      low - starting index of the subarray
      high - ending index of the subarray
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • partition

      private int partition(T[] shapes, int low, int high, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Helper method for quick sort that partitions the array. Places pivot at its correct position in sorted array and places all smaller elements to left of pivot, and all greater elements to right of pivot.
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be partitioned
      low - starting index of the subarray
      high - ending index of the subarray
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering
      Returns:
      the partitioning index

    • heapSort

      public void heapSort(T[] shapes, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Heap sort implementation. Creates a max heap of the array and repeatedly extracts the maximum element. Time Complexity: O(n log n) Space Complexity: O(1)
      Parameters:
      shapes - array to be sorted
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering

    • heapify

      private void heapify(T[] shapes, int n, int i, Comparator<T> comparator)
      Helper method for heap sort that heapifies a subtree rooted with node i. Assumes that the subtrees are already heapified.
      Parameters:
      shapes - array representing heap
      n - size of heap
      i - root node of subtree
      comparator - comparator to determine ordering
